<m0>   Greenwich Air Services said net income rose 76 percent in its second quarter, primarily because of higher sales and lower interest expense.<ep>
   Net sales rose 36 percent in the quarter, the company said. Meanwhile, about $13 million in 8 percent convertible debt was converted to stock in the first and second quarters, saving the company about $300,000 a quarter in interest expense.<ep>
   Greenwich said it expects its $250 million acquisition of Aviall's engine maintenance division to be completed by the end of June.<ep>
   Last week, the company declared a dividend of one share of Class B non-voting stock for each share of Class A common stock. A new issue of additional Class B stock is expected to raise about $75 million, to help finance the acquisition.<ql>
