<m1><styl>txt,14p<ql>
<ep>
<m0>  Unite, the Union of Needletrades, Industrial and Textile Employees, said the licensed practical nurses at Hebrew Home for the Aged in North Miami Beach have voted to unionize.<ep>
   The vote count among the bargaining unit of 15 nurses was 12-0, the union said. The home's staff of about 60 nursing assistants, housekeepers and laundry and food workers voted in March to unionize, although the home has filed objections to the vote with the National Labor Relations Board.<ep>
   ``This will be an inspiration for other nurses in nursing homes across Florida,'' said Monica Russo, southern organizing director for Unite.<ep>
