<m0>  Servico, a West Palm Beach-based hotel operator, said Friday it has refinanced debt on 20 of its 58 hotels and will put the $31.5 million in proceeds toward buying more hotels. The $123.2 million in new debt is on hotels in Florida and 12 other states.<ep>
   Chief executive David Buddemeyer said the net would be used to reach the company's goal of acquiring $100 million in hotel properties this year. He also said Lehman Brothers Holdings, the lender in the refinancing, ``has indicated a willingness to participate in the financing'' of the acquisitions.<ep>
   Servico has primarily full-service hotels affiliated with national chains in 20 states and Puerto Rico. With more than $350 million in assets, the company is one of the largest hotel owner/operators in the United States.<ql>
